Louis,<br>
I am a professional soldier--born to a career NCO on a Horse Cavalry Post.  I am qualified as a real &quot;lifer.&quot; &lt;G&gt;Talk about change&lt;G&gt;  <br>
    I am Armor officer and I served as the Senior Advisor to the ARVN 7rh Cav. Regt in 1967.  The 7th opeated in the Hue--Quang Tri [includes the Street Withou Joy].  <br>
    The 7th was the first ARVN Cav unit to receive the US Presidential Unit Citation.   Good outfit and good people.<br>
     As a side note, my counterpart was captured after the fall and spent 15 years in a &quot;re-education&quot; camp.  Apon his release he tried to join his family in the States but the Gov't wouldn't let him go--for free.  <br>
    Two other former Advisors and myself, tried to get some--any--help from the US Gov--got zilch.  So the three of us got $3,000 together to &quot;ransum&quot; him and he's living in Calif now.  We correspond.<br>
    If you'd like his addresse, you can E-Mail me at:<br>
Tanker6525@aol.com  I was in VN when Fall steped on a mine--on &quot;The Street Without Joy&quot;---a trail really.  His book is still the best on the French part of the war.<br>
  PS---Know about the weather.  <br>
